text:
four more days til the daddies comes out and i want to say, wow, it's not for everyone. it's full of #sex and #violence and is meant to be a bit #disturbing in a familiar, also #arousing way. the first friend who read a draft thought the writing was good but was so upset and disgusted by it there were parts she couldn't read. overall, she hated it. i put it away for nearly a year after, until i started to realize that such a #passionate response surely meant something that i should investigate further, despite the it being painful. glad i finished it. i hope you will be too... "#feminist in its worldmaking, #intellectual in its #erotic #poetry, and razor sharp in its depictions of contemporary american gender ideology, kimberly dark's the daddies is a complex and genre-bending contribution to the archive of #queer feeling and to theorizing through #storytelling. in this autoethnography of daddy's worlds, the girls who inhabit and work in them are allowed to examine pleasures and pains of power and contradiction. taking a range of positions, dark's writing dares to interrogate the #psychic structures and deep ambivalences of a queer desire and kinship form in ways that move us beyond simplistic ideas of perversion and subversion. the daddies is a welcome addition to fem(me)inist sexual theory and a portrait of contemporary patriarchy by and for daddy's girls, by and author who has lived and survived and dared to tell. plus we learn more about what is at the root of #metoo and its perpetual reproductions from this book than many other contemporary sources. - ulrika dahl professor of gender studies at uppsala university, co-author of femmes of power: exploding queer femininities (hashtags are mine) @brillpublishing

text:
earlier this month, 67-year-old don palmerine came forward about a rape he witnessed and participated in 1969, almost five decades prior. his reason for coming forward decades later is rooted in the #metoo movement.

in a penned essay for the washington post, palmerine recalls the fuzzy night, admitting that though he fails to remember the trivial details of the night, he does remember the distinct “before and after” of the disturbing event.

on sunday (oct. 21), palmerine spoke to michel martin of npr’s “all things considered,” to speak further on his decision to come forward. published soon after the heartbreaking testimony of dr. christine blasey ford in the brett kavanaugh hearings, palmerine confirms that ford was the motivation for the piece, finding resolution in her “genuine” testimony. not only did he feel that ford “was really telling the truth,” but he was also able to relate to ford, having also experienced trivial gaps in his memory from the dark night.

having attended an all-boys uppity catholic high school in pittsburg, pennsylvania, an invitation to attend the party was extended to palmerine by a football player from a nearby all-boys catholic school. in an attempt to impress the jocks, palmerine accepted the invitation only to find that “there were far more boys than girls at this party” and that “other than the girls,” no one was drinking. “at one point, a boy told several of us to go outside and look through a window into the basement because another boy, a football player, had taken a girl there. when we peered through, we saw the girl passed out on a sofa, her feet facing us. as the boy approached her, he waved to us, smiling. he proceeded to remove her jeans and then her underwear. it was the first time i had seen a girl naked. he climbed on top of her and penetrated her. she immediately woke up and tried to fight him off. at this point, we all scattered in the yard. no one said anything. there was just nervous laughter.” source:vibe.com

⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
please read this if you’re women
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
have you heard of ‘molka'?
‘molka’ is a korean word that means ‘spy cam.'
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
korean men are sexually excited about secretly filming the bodies of women (including their female family members - mom, daughter, sister, wife), and secretly filming pictures of women peeing or shitting, even though it is an obvious crime.
hidden cameras capture women undressing, going to the toilet, or even in changing rooms in clothing stores, gyms and swimming pools.
the videos are posted online on pop-up pornography sites.
even though the victims are reporting the site and asking the uploader to remove it, it never works.
if serious, victims even attempt suicide and sometimes succeed in killing themselves, but the watchers call the video posthumous work or masterpiece.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
the problem is not just the ‘molka.'
men who commit sex crimes in korea sentenced to less than five years in prison or a very small fine.
in addition, most victims of sexual violence choose to commit suicide due to the secondary victimization and trauma.
in south korea, most #metoo activists (who were sexually assaulted) are suffering from a secondary offense by korean men.
korea is not a country that women can live in. 
it is only a country for men.
if you are reading this post, and if you are a woman, 
please do not come to south korea.
also, please tell this story to your acquaintance who wants to visit korea.

text:
beautiful girl, you can do hard things! ✨
.

this is me before i started valuing myself as a woman. i used food as my comfort and excess weight as my protection, topping the scale at 215. i had a secret that i was tormented by and ashamed of. sexual assault made me feel that i wasn’t worthy of protection or value. .

i wish i could go back and hold that precious girl and tell her it wasn’t her fault. that she was and is more valuable than diamonds and rubies. .

my transformation is about way more than some numbers on a scale, more than inches gained or lost, and more than body fat percentages. it is about choosing myself as a worthy, strong, beautiful child of god who has an identity so much bigger than her past. .

my journey is far from perfect. it is full of ups and downs and days of being scared of losing weight because it triggers my need for protection. control of my environment. each day more layers are shed and i am seeing a new me. not a victim, not ashamed, not broken. 
strong.
powerful.
worthy.
beautiful.
courageous. .
one step at a time, getting up each time there’s a stumble. one foot in front of the other, because i am worth it. 
you are worth it, babe. 💕
.
.
.
.
#transformation #beauty #worthy #beachbodycoach #beforeandafter #fitness #zumbafitness #metoo #strong #badasswomen #journey #80dayobsession #lift4 #healing 
#weightlosstransformation #weightlossjourney

text: a student asked libby larsen in masterclass, "what has changed for women composers over the course of your career, and what challenges do they still face?" after watching her with such energy and enthusiasm for two hours, suddenly she began and cut off a few thoughts, then explained, "you see, i'm stammering now because this makes me very angry and i have a lot to say." to paraphrase, she answered, "direct rejection is no longer acceptable. when i was a graduate student, you could say, 'you can't do this because you're woman.' you can't do that anymore. now we have things like the #metoo movement which show you how long things have been going on and how they are still. but apart from that, not much has changed. women composers still face marginalization and benign negligence. i was taught to keep asking direct questions until you get answers, sit in the road and refuse to move, wear black and stand tall, and don't play games. let your brilliance and your talent show." #composertales #shewritesmusic #womenwritemusic #womencomposers

text:
last year’s #metoo movement was not just a voice for sexual harassment, it also began to help shed light onto the issue of adult bullying, a real problem! one studying showing that 31% had experienced bullying themselves and 45% felt that it was becoming more accepted. which is a scary number considering the impact it can leave on someone’s life & health. 
not just in the moment but long term effects such as, sleep loss, anxiety, depression, $$ lost to sick days, stress from the bullying causing muscle pain, thyroid issues, high blood pressure, mood disorders, self harming and eating disorders. 
a study done by the american journal of public health issued in 2015 showed that victims of workplace bullying have double the risk of suicidal ideation of the subsequent 5 years! 
we may think of bullying and think kids, teenagers... and yes! that is very true, it’s an on going war we fight for our children. 
but it’s also happening to moms and dads. it’s a very serious problem one that because they are adults they may feel shame and embarrassment, causing them to not seek out the help they need. 
let’s help put an end to any stigmas of adult bullying, take it seriously, and stand up against it!!! •
•
•

agera som en kvinna. 💝
tänk som en man.
inget kan jämföras med en kvinnas kärlek. hon är generös med sin omtanke, är vårdande och har tålamod. hon tar hand om sin familj med uppmuntran och medkänsla. hon håller många bollar i luften. hon ger av hela sitt hjärta.
är du hennes man vet du att du ska vara tankeläsare och en god lyssnare. hon pratar tills det inte finns ord kvar att säga och då, just då, ska du finnas där och förstå. oavsett om det är ”den veckan” eller hon ”är hungrig” så har hon rätt. hon vet var skåpet ska stå och det ser du väl att det passar bäst så. hon ger sitt stöd fastän hon inte förstår alla dina idéer. om det så är navelludd här och där. eller femtioelva ficklampor som kan komma till användning. ( jo men visst ; )
om du är hennes man och du älskar henne, försvara henne i alla lägen och tänk smart. du vet att hon agerar som kvinna. hon är kvinna. tänk då som en man. en gentleman. du vet hur hon fungerar, du vet vad som händer och du vet också vart skåpet står bäst. ge henne extra mycket kärlek och en chokladbit. förlåt, fel av mig, ge henne en hel chokladkaka. vill du vara på den säkra sidan? ge henne en hel chokladask.

text:
u.s. actress #amberheard, a star of the upcoming "aquaman" superhero movie and a u.n. human rights champion, said on monday her childhood in texas near the mexican border helped spark her activism.
"going home in his pickup truck, there was an "indelible impression left on my soul", a recognition of injustice and unfairness for children on the mexican side."
"simply due to where i was born, a few miles north of this line, i was free to travel back and forth as i saw fit," she told an audience at the united nations in geneva on monday. "thousands of others would risk everything "for a mere shot and an opportunity to have that which i was just awarded due to this accidental luck of my birth on the other side. that was when i first started to pick up on the sensation."
"social media now gives everybody the chance to change things, with online campaigns like #metoo, time's up, and black lives matter, and while hollywood had a responsibility to lead, it had failed to do so, she said."
"there is a certain amount of irony in the sense that hollywood is often held up as some sort of bastion of progressive ideals, yet is actually in reality the exact opposite." "on some of the most basic rights that we are starting, thank goodness, to take for granted in other disciplines, in other businesses, whether it is inclusion, pay equality, representation, diversity, you name it, we fall way behind." @amberheard 👏👏 @channelnewsasia #humanrights  #standup4humanrights #sams #syrianrefugees #lgbtqi #lgbtqirights #unitednations #unitednationshumanrights #rightsandactivism #storytelling #librarytalks #unoglibrary  #ambassador #actress #activist #mera #aquaman #dceu #superhero #dccfans #dccfilms #dccmovies #dccomics #geneva

text: on the latest episode of the lunch table podcast, the table gets a surprise visit from star basketball player, maurice watson jr. having led creighton to the number 7 rank in the ncaa with a 17-1 record, maurice tragically tore his acl in the 19th game of his final collegiate season. from there, it all went south for maurice as he suddenly found himself being accused of sexually assaulting a fellow student at creighton. we explore maurice's trials and tribulations during his return from injury, falsified sexual assault accusations, and countless other set backs. maurice provides us insight into the raw details of his rough upbringing in philly, his split collegiate basketball career at both boston university and creighton, his road to recovery, and his painful and eye-opening experiences dealing with the us justice system during the apex of the #metoo movement. maurice highlights the importance of concrete friendships, his family, and an unwavering faith in god. he is now playing professional basketball in the fiba europe cup league and still maintains his childhood dream of playing in the nba. the maurice watson story has only been told to the lunch table podcast, so tune in for this rollercoaster ride of emotions! (episode link in the bio) @jaygillythekid @thelunchtablepc @gdiddy210 @mauricewatson10 @rawtruthradio

text:
save the dates for our upcoming 'art in context' lecture series!⠀
oct 30 | 12:00 p.m. art lecture: "inspired to act: why young women combat sexism" ⠀
women have taken action against sexual assault by joining movements such as #metoo. this lecture presented by jennifer thomas, wilkes associate professor of psychology, examines why some women take action while others do not and how factors may influence a feminist identity.⠀
⠀
nov 7 | 4:30 p.m. art lecture: "out of silence: activism and empathy in the art of elizabeth catlett,"⠀
the art of elizabeth catlett is grounded in what she regarded as the historically based necessity to give voice to the lives and experiences of those who have historically been forced into silence. this lecture presented by melanie herzog, dean of the school of arts & sciences and professor of art history at edgewood college, will examine what catlett believed art could do: raise consciousness of injustice, expose abuses of power, and illuminate possibilities for social transformation.⠀
⠀

text:
"going home in his pickup truck, there was an “indelible impression left on my soul”, a recognition of injustice and unfairness for children on the mexican side."
“simply due to where i was born, a few miles north of this line, i was free to travel back and forth as i saw fit,” she told an audience at the united nations in geneva on monday. thousands of others would risk everything “for a mere shot and an opportunity to have that which i was just awarded due to this accidental luck of my birth on the other side. that was when i first started to pick up on the sensation.”
social media now gives everybody the chance to change things, with online campaigns like #metoo, time’s up, and black lives matter, and while hollywood had a responsibility to lead, it had failed to do so, she said.
“there is a certain amount of irony in the sense that hollywood is often held up as some sort of bastion of progressive ideals, yet is actually in reality the exact opposite. “on some of the most basic rights that we are starting, thank goodness, to take for granted in other disciplines, in other businesses, whether it is inclusion, pay equality, representation, diversity, you name it, we fall way behind.” @amberheard 🙌 pic by @toddkrim ☀️ #amberheard #actress #activist #ambassador #unitednations #standup4humanrights #humanrights #mera #aquaman #hero #superhero #inspiration #dccfans #dccmovies #dccomicsmovies #dccomicsfans #dcmovies #dcc #dceu

text_retweet:
reposting to keep fresh: let me make it clear: there is no, none, zip, zero, working class party in america that can currently save us from the two corporate parties running us dry while the 1% collect the money from our work. i’ve been reading chris hedges book “death of the liberal class,” and it’s really made me look at our current situation. we have two wall street parties, two pro war parties, two pro-fossil fuel parties (like it or not the dems are barely any better, they flipped on taking donations from the fossil fuel industry within a month of pledging not to.) we have two parties that work in the interest of the few while the many suffer to get by. i’m not calling for violence but i’m saying that we cannot continue down this path of allowing small incremental changes to be enough. we need radical change that will benefit the masses and not just the few.
.
.

text:
love letter monday
•
i was anorexic for 15 years. then, one day, it dawned on me that in a world that profits off the insecurity, timidity, and voicelessness of women, not only had my self-hatred been programmed into me, but my loyalty to that programming was complicity. so, rejecting that ingrained self-hatred would be — is — a riotous act of revolution. as a woman, loving oneself is an act of feminism. it is change, embodied.
•
in a world that feeds and functions on our smallness, dare to be bold.
•
dare to love.
dare to speak.
dare to demand space.
dare to grow.
dare to lead.
•
woman by woman, body by body, this is how we rise.
•
it is time.
•
love, reema
•
❤️
•
#lovelettermonday #loveletter #iamyours #memoir #mondaymotivation #anorexiarecovery #writersofinstagram #artistsoninstagram #authorsofinstagram  #selflove #love #itistime #metoo #womenempowerment 📸@erikaellisphotography
name: Reema Zaman

please don’t catcall. even to be funny. don’t make someone else feel uncomfortable or terrified for their life intentionally.}

text:
music composer anu malik has stepped down from the jury panel of singing reality show, indian idol, a statement from sony entertainment television read. malik has been accused of sexual harassment by multiple women amid the #metoo movement raging across the country.

the television channel’s statement says a replacement will be found for him who will join the other two judges on the show, vishal dadlani & neha kakkar. “anu malik is no longer a part of indian idol jury panel. the show will continue its planned schedule & we’ll invite some of the biggest names in indian music as guests to join vishal & neha to judge extraordinary talent of indian idol season 10,” the statement read.

malik also shared a statement saying he is taking a break from the show. “i, anu malik, have decided to take a break from indian idol as i am currently unable to focus on my work on the show. the channel has been kind to agree for the same. thank you,” malik said.

after singers sona mohapatra & shweta pandit accused malik of sexual harassment, two budding singers levelled similar allegations against him.

shweta had said in her post that she was just 15 when malik made her uncomfortable by asking to kiss him. “had to go back to my worst memory as a teenage girl today to write this & speak up – its now or never. this is my #metoo & have to warn young girls about #anumalik & let you know your #timesup @indiametoo. thank you @sonamohapatra for speaking up about him & supporting this,” she wrote on twitter.

earlier, in an instagram post, singer sona mahapatra wrote, “to all the young girls & women who are coming out with their experiences with this creep, journalists, ‘fans’ & even kids from college, know that you are not alone. this guy, #kailashkher is a serial predator & has been for years as are many others like anu malik in the industry. i cannot be tweeting about everyone cus i work 18 hour work days & have a life to live & breathe in.” sona had tweeted again on saturday saying by not taking action against malik, makers of the show are complicit.

a lawyer for the music director thursday denied the claims against him, saying india’s #metoo movement is being used for his client’s

text:
dear men,
from a very young age i was taught that i should speak softly, be polite, submissive, etc. etc. you basically want me to be, how you so politely put it, accommodating.

you think i am so weak that it's become your 'thing' to insinuate that i am the one who is okay with this present trend of rape culture. 
someone said that i am like "fresh meat". and when said "fresh meat" is left in the open, the dogs are tempted to have it. you say that this is why one should keep the said "meat" inside the house. but what if i say that you should tie up your dogs? that's a better idea, isn't it?

you think that i am the one who provokes you to rape me by just walking on the streets at 9 p.m. but don't you think that it's kind of embarrassing that you are turned on just by the idea of me walking? i mean dude, ever heard of self control?  and then you say i'm desperate.

you parade about with the agenda of "disciplining" me by raping me and saying that you're doing me a favour.  what if i start doing the same? what if the next time i see you walking around the streets at 9 p.m. and decide that you need to be taught a lesson? 
my idea sounds cringy. even barbaric. right? it sounds the same when you say it. 
i want this to be a message to all of you out there. i accept who i am and i don't give a single flying fuck about what you think.

so yeah, i am not sorry that i'm a girl.
from, 
a female human © mystic🍁
(p.s. this writing is also posted on the #ttt app on #imnotsorry)

text:
here’s one about #mentalhealth- 
when i think about my #depression, i think about this photo. this girl had just been told that she was “not fun to be around,” that “no one wanted to spend time with her” and that a man especially would only put up with being around her “for one thing.” she was manipulated, she was verbally, mentally and emotionally abused. she was pushed and pulled and blamed and sometimes loved and worshipped as though nothing bad had happened. when this photo was taken, she was completely broken, has lost a staggering amount of weight from stress and didn’t recognize herself. somehow, in some moment coerced by nicole, this genuine smile happened. i’m pretty certain it was a hysterical laugh at my situation, but i like to see it as a glimmer of hope. i see myself as truly beautiful because it shows the spark that i still had within me. a spark which, though i did go back to this man only weeks later, allowed me to finally stand up for myself. 
it’s been years. my confidence is still shaken. i still doubt that anyone ever genuinely wants to spend time with me, but each day i get better. 
most of my followers know this man. several of them shared that wonderful “if i am friends with your abuser, let me know and i will unfriend them” post that was going around. i somehow only found the strength to say his name to one of them. the rest continue to praise him, unknowing. 
sharing today to praise the other women who have #stoodup, said #timesup and #metoo and victims of #abusiverelationships including #mentalabuse #emotionalabuse and #sexualabuse. remember: check on your strong friends. find your glimmer of #hope and hold on. 
photo credit: @shesophoto
name: Mackenzie Newbury

text:
on the latest episode of the lunch table podcast, the table gets a surprise visit from star basketball player, @mauricewatson10. having led @bluejaymbb to the number 7 rank in the @ncaasports with a 17-1 record, maurice tragically tore his acl in the 19th game of his final collegiate season. from there, it all went south for maurice as he suddenly found himself being accused of sexually assaulting a fellow student at #creighton. we explore maurice's trials and tribulations during his return from injury, falsified sexual assault accusations, and countless other set backs. maurice provides us insight into the raw details of his rough upbringing in #philadelphia, his split collegiate basketball career at both @bostonu and creighton, his road to recovery, and his painful and eye-opening experiences dealing with the #us justice system during the apex of the #metoo movement. maurice highlights the importance of concrete friendships, his family, and an unwavering faith in #god. he is now playing professional #basketball in the #fiba europe cup league and still maintains his childhood dream of playing in the @nba. the maurice watson story has only been told to the lunch table podcast, so tune in for this rollercoaster ride of emotions! (episode link in the bio) 
#soundcloud: https://soundcloud.com/thelunchtablepodcast/maurice-watson-episode

#itunes: https://itunes.apple.com/us/podcast/the-lunch-table-podcast/id1206993614?mt=2#episodeguid=tag%3asoundcloud%2c2010%3atracks%2f518013117

cc: @yahoosports @espn @bleacherreport @cbssports @sportsillustrated @nbcsports @sbnation @foxsports @rantsports @deadspin @thepostgame @playerstribune @klutchsports @uninterrupted @kingjames @richpaul @rawtruthradio

text:
sexual assault can happen anywhere to anyone. according to rainn, 55% of sexual assaults happen at or near the victims house, 15% in an open public space, 12% at or near a relative’s home, 10% in enclosed or public area such as a parking lot or garage, and 8% on school property.
safety tip: trust your gut. if you feel unsafe or uncomfortable, ask for help or leave. have someone escort you to your car or call a friend to come get you if you don’t feel safe.

text:
darling, you feel heavy because you are too full of truth. open your mouth more and let the truth exist somewhere other than inside your body. - della hicks-wilson
.
this weekend at the @theuncommonwoman live event shook me from head to toe.
.
standing up sharing my story released a powerful vibration within me. knowing that i am walking my truth and reality i create everyday.
.
every speaker and every word they spoke left a mark with each of us so powerful and healing. this weekend was truly magic. all together as uncommon women & men.
.
i am so full of gratitude and love for this experience and each connection made this weekend. this movement is like no other. i am so blessed to be a part of it and to be witness to it. .
incredibly blessed to have the amazing support and love crom@my family as they have witnessed and supported me during my journey. no words to express my full love for all this.
.
i am so looking toward to the future, sharing more. standing in stages more and impacting more. my path never been so clear as what i need to do next. my passion to inspire others like me to have the #pwr2change.
.
.
.

text_retweet:
today i release all resistence of the past and move into the present moment

often times we are hunted by the mistakes we have made in our past. we live in bondage to our past pain, traumas and actions that we are not proud of.

we have believed the lie that we must be perfect without flaws for so long that we have no idea that human perfection is an illusion.

we are spiritual beings having an human experience to expand in conciousness. soul expansion evolves from conquering our problems, overcoming our fears and growing from lessons learned. 
i call the “devil” those self-defeating behaviors and thoughts that cause us to hold ourselves in bondage to lack of self love and resistence to change. what we resist persist.

fear is the greatest devil of them all. it is usually fear that causes guilt and shame. 
we are afraid of what people will think of us if they knew this flaw. fear of what could happen if i made this change in my life. fear of what could go wrong or who will be disappointed.

we must stop worrying about what others think about us & our lives and focus more on failing ourselves if we don’t live the life we know we desire deep down inside.

the only way to begin to live that life is to break the chains of the past and move forward into our future with no regrets and know that the things that happened to us or the mistakes we made in the past is what propels us into greatness and thru our tests emerges our testimony to inspire others.

take the lesson as a blessing and move forward in gratitude for growth.

stop holding on to what is hindering and gravitate towards what will honor our highest and greatest self.

this is the realization the main character monee had to come to grips with in the book i wrote, “the devils bedroom.” the main charcter monee, had to discover that self love is self acceptance – all of it – the good and the bad.

in order to heal… the chains of guilt and shame must be broken with self love and forgiveness.

today i release all resistence of the past and move into the present moment

#lightworker
#selflove
#collectiveconsciousness
#letstalkaboutitandheal
#thedevilsbedroom
#healing
#souljourney 
#metoo

text:
i just won the season 7 of all india corporate talent championship for solo dance ❤❤so happy. the competition was judged by @marzipestonji and @anushkadisco and their comments for my performance were truly humbling. i am glad i could do justice to this theme that i chose. 
with the #metoo movement, i wanted to bring to notice, the sexual harassment of men. why do we ridicule a man who is sexually harassed. we ridicule him more if he is violated by a woman. is it correct to question his masculinity?
this is the story of one such guy who is violated by a family member (gender of the offender is not revealed) the guy tries to resist and tell it to people, but he is threatened and ridiculed and muted by social pressure to meet his fateful judgement. 
i hope you like the performance and take harassment of men as seriously as that of women. 
let's not make this a battle of genders, it is never us vs them, we have enough discrimination, let's support each other for what is right. you're not alone..it is  #youandmetoo ❤
thanks to all the participants who supported me so much. i really appreciate it ❤❤
thanks for the video @deshreyas

text:
review of “bernhardt/hamlet” part 2 of 2.
.
rebeck’s bernhardt is a complex creature. she has ego, ambition, and gravitas, but she also has immense fear of failure and self-doubt. she enjoys fame, praise, and admiration yet demands respect, privacy, and discretion. she may be a woman but she is not submissive. she may be beautiful but she is not delicate. she may be an actress but she is not stupid. bernhardt is aware of her power and presence and she knows exactly what to do with them.
.
the dazzling janet mcteer is captivating as bernhardt. she is sensual, playful, and magnetic. mcteer’s real power isn’t fully harnessed until act two, but it is worth the wait. in bernhardt’s confrontation scene with her lover, playwright edmond rostand (cleverly played by jason butler harner), i swear, mcteer stopped the room. no one moved or made a sound until she took one last disappointed, broken hearted look at rostand and closed the door behind her.
.
this play has much to offer a 21st century audience. you don’t need to know anything about bernhardt, shakespeare, or 19th century france to enjoy it or to get something out of it. it may not be the sexiest or the easiest play on #broadway right now, but i suppose that depends on your perspective and your willingness. but in the age of #metoo, #womensreality, and #nastywoman, who wouldn’t want to see a play about a woman who stands up for herself and fights for what she wants; a woman who does things her own way and refuses to back down just because a man tells her “no.”
.
#theresarebek #bernhardthamlet #janetmcteer #roundabouttheatre #broadway #theater #theatre
📷: @roundaboutnyc

text:
hey guys. 
so, @ronnyonkeo & i are thinking of creating a scream platform, and we need your voices.
do you want to share your personal stories about any form of sexual harassment, from the mildest incidents to the harshest? 
we want to hear you. 
any story really, even one of you defending yourself, or someone else defending you. 
this is your platform. we are slowly building it, stone by stone. for you. for all of us. 
if you so wish, your identity will remain purely hidden. 
we want your stories, we want to tell them to the world, show them that this is happening & we need to stop it. 
inbox me if you're interested in this, any part of it, really. 
even with tips & whatnot. 
also, my dm is still a safe space, and my house will be a home for you. if you need to just talk, we can drink coffee or whiskey or just plain water, i'll be here, to listen, and to help. 
#scream
#enough
#metoo

text:
survivors of childhood sexual abuse hide their emotions from the world to protect themselves from being labeled, stigmatized or judge about the things that happened to them as children. i remember wearing a different mask every day just to fit in with the world. but when i returned home after a long day of acting behind a mask i would again become that wounded little child. i would curl up in a ball and cry myself to sleep every night. every day i struggled to hide the things that were destroying me inside from my childhood. today i choose to no longer hide my feelings or put on a mask to fit in or to be part of the world. if the world accepts me for who i am or not is not my concern anymore. i have to live my truth no matter what happens. no more masks. no more silence.  i am me raw, authentic and a survivor.

cecibel contreras
isuvoa.com

text: killen som skickade dickpicks till mig är nu polisanmäld. jag var påväg att skriva en lång förklaring till varför jag var så dum som öppnade meddelandet överhuvudtaget. och jag insåg att jag återigen skäms för att blivit utsatt! att jag känner att jag måste förklara mig.. jag känner skuld och skam trots att jag vet att den inte är min att bära. jag tar ansvar för något jag inte gjort. text:
thrilled to have lara bundock present on the panel after our film screening. please join us at the broadway theater in nottingham england on october 30th for this special screening.
lara bundock is the founding ceo of ‘the snowdrop project’. after training as a social worker, she practiced in an nrm safe house and was shocked by the lack of available support after the nrm. seeing previous clients become homeless, develop debt, drug and alcohol problems or become missing people; she designed a social work based support programme to address clients ongoing needs. the project grew to include counselling, community activities, a house renovation service and pathways to education/employment. lara co-authored ‘life beyond the safe house’ (2015) and has spoken around the uk, northern ireland and turkmenistan about working with survivors of trafficking. she is passionate about needs-led support being available nationwide following methods of best practice and equipping others to understand the complex needs of survivors.

text:
human trafficking is a process of enslaving people, coercing them into a situation with no way out, and exploiting them. --------------------------------------------------------•51% of identified victims of trafficking are women, 28% children and 21% men.
•72% people exploited in the sex industry are women.
•63% of identified traffickers were men and 37% women.
•43% of victims are trafficked domestically within national borders.

when we look at human trafficking, we always think that it's far away from us.
meanwhile it's a lot more closer to home. let's raise our voices louder, fight this epidemic and take our freedom back. ✊🏻✊🏼✊🏽✊🏾✊🏿 @unwomen #yoursistersspace

text:
in discussion with @zoomtv about abuse of power, and what it means. why women don’t speak up, and why we as a society judge women for doing what they do, even though we do not judge the men abusing their power. ask yourself how often you look at a new actress and say ‘she must’ve fucked her way on top’, but at the same time, we don’t look at the men that are casting them and say ‘i wonder how often he has abused his power to misuse girls.’ she does it even though she shouldn’t have to, and you slut shame her. 
he does it, and you say ‘so many sluts are ready to give in’
really?
the same logic applies when we talk about physical or sexual abuse towards women all over our society. we judge the victim, we dissect her character, we refuse to believe her story. 
for those that are still confused, #metoo is about work place assault, it is also about psychical and sexual abuse in relationships. me too is about a woman’s right to be treated equally. the campaign started by people in media to bring sexism in the industry to lime light - but that doesn’t mean its limited to work places. 
please stop asking women to ‘limit’ their assault stories to one space, as though if she’s been raped or beaten at home, it’s no longer me too. that’s the worst thing you could to do a movement this large and sensitive, tell women their stories of abuse are not important.
me too, is about empowering women. all women, everywhere.
me too, is about empowering women.

text:
milkman review: the pleasure derived from this book is akin to a strenuous round of exercise — you will feel exerted, tired, spent, tinged with an endorphin-induced afterglow. 
_
the setting: a community in northern ireland during the time of the troubles — “knife-edged times, primal times, with everybody suspicious of everybody”. people are divided between “renouncers” versus “defenders” — “this side of the road” versus “that side of the road” — subjected to bomb scares, hijackings, paramilitary rule, kangaroo courts, surveillance, and endless cycles of revenge and counter-revenge. unwritten rules of allegiance dictate the names you give your children, the television programs you are permitted to watch, the brands of food you eat, the shops you frequent, the hymns you sing, the bus stop you use:
_
“there was the fact that you created a political statement everywhere you went, and with everything you did, even if you didn’t want to.”
_
naturally, such an intense climate of tribalism and communal self-policing leaves very little room for individual expression.
_
enter our narrator, a young irish woman living on the renouncer side of the community. she is seen as an outcast, declared “beyond-the-pale”, due to her fondness for “reading-while-walking” — a deliberate ritual to escape the political mental space by losing herself in 19th century literature. she has nine siblings and a mother who continually harangues her to get married. when a prominent paramilitary figures, dubbed “milkman”, becomes sexually interested in her, his insistent attentions and subtle means of psychological manipulation start to chisel away at her sense of self.
_
onto the language: there is a freedom and plasticity to burns’ writing that echoes thought. at times, in an intense burst of proustian introspection, the narrative zooms in on a single moment in time, letting it mushroom to fill twenty pages of descriptive text. at other times, the narration is inflected with an austenian tick — a nod to the narrator’s 19th century literary diet — with its fondness for circumlocution. a liar is a “teller of untruths”. mad people are “creatures of another planet...”
_
(continued in comments 👇🏻)

text:
content: includes sexual harassment/assault, slut shaming, transphobia, christianity •
•
tonight i’ll be loving this flesh shell that so many people have shamed and covered, commented on without permission, touched without permission, restricted, and punished. my dress code violation act is angry, vengeful, irreverent, sad, and sexy... just like me. it’s for my ex who was embarrassed of my “inappropriate” and “provocative” red crop top (spoiler alert: i’m wearing it in the act). it’s for the churches i grew up in that told me “not to make boys stumble” by having visible bra straps. it’s for the school admin who told me my clothing was in violation of dress code last spring, after i introduced myself as a guest speaker. it’s for the woman who, when i tried to report a sexual assault, told me “women don’t hire strippers unless they want extra services.” it’s for my alma mater @azusapacific that continues to oppress students’ trans and queer bodies. it’s for someone being told to “put their boobs away” at work. it’s for the person at sf pride who told me he “almost just grabbed [my] ass” (and for @teasesandties who told him she’d gouge his eyes out). it’s to reclaim some space at dna lounge after a man cornered me behind a merch table, hand down his pants. it’s because i’ve been having dreams almost nightly this week that i’m being sexually assaulted. it’s for dr. ford, anita hill. it’s for a loved one who was recently told by an older man that he thought it was “really hot she was reading in a bar.” it’s for my friends who are grabbed in bars, followed home, swung at on bart, yelled at from cars, misgendered by lyft drivers, sexually harassed at work, slut shamed, victim blamed, fetishized, gaslighted, told they’re in a phase or confused, interrupted, co-opted, belittled, told they’re too angry or aggressive... i could go on. so many of us have bodies/existences that are constantly surveilled and regulated and picked apart - i’m talking about trans folks, brown and black folks, undocumented folks, queer folks, women, youth. •
i love this silly, fragile, resilient, naked old thing. i don’t need permission, make my own decisions... it’s my prerogative.

text:
only 310 of out of every 1,000 sexual assault cases are reported to the authorities. which means that about 2 out of 3 sexual assaults cases aren’t reported. you may be asking yourself, why don’t victims report their assault? this is because victims are silenced. victims are silenced by fear. fear of their abuser, fear of what others will think of them, fear of their personal experience being talked about, fear of the names they will be called and the questions they will be asked. it’s not as easy as just telling a police officer what happened. people question you and ask you things like, “why didn’t you try harder to get out of the situation?”, and they say that they don’t believe you, that the person who abused you would never do something like that. this is the america we live in. where a victim finally finds the courage to speak up and is condemned, judged, and silenced. this has to end. we need to change this world. we need to listen to victims and provide them with love and believe their stories. if you are a victim of sexual assault, i encourage you to speak up about your situation and stand strong. because you are strong. you can get through this and you are not alone. together, we can all unite and empower victims to stand strong with courage. we can believe them and listen to them. we can change this america that we are currently living in, one step at a time. #whyididntreport #metoo #survivors #believesurvivors

if anyone needs someone to talk to, please dm me. i am here for you!❤️

text:
we have a lot of new friends here so i thought i would take a second to introduce myself.
.
👋🏻 my name is taryn you can call me “taryndactyle” “taryn it up” or “tarynasaures rex” 😂.
.
 i am a momma of a crazy cute 3 year old. wife, business owner, keto diet lifer, positivity addict and  i consider myself a self hate survivor!
.
in my spare time:
lol if spare time exists, i love to wander target, watch football (go lions), go on a date with the hubbs or adventure with my little man. .
my style:
i decided i am a little bit casual country and a little bit rock n roll.
.
something i struggle with:
loving myself! being a heavier girl my entire life and living with a self hate mentality. i have to constantly practice positive self talk and remember how far i have come! 70 lbs lost has been tough on my mind but also so amazing for my health. 🙌🏻
.
something shocking about me:
i am a cancer and sexual assault survivor. i don’t feel like those things define me as a person. however, they have really helped me to become a strong women that knows i can get through anything life throws my way. 👊🏻
.
i would love to get to know you all! what is something you love to do in your spare time? .
.
.
.

text:
lekker gewerkt mannen! en leuk om terug te zien, het house rules #keuken project in amersfoort.
.
morgenavond helpen we vanaf 20:30u een nieuw koppel aan hun massief houten keukenfrontjes (op dinsdag en woensdag 23 + 24 oktober). beter kijkt u dus weer naar house rules op net5. zien jullie misschien onze wouter ook nog even! oeh! 👯
.
keukenfronten dus. we maken ze praktisch voor iedere keuken. in de gewenste groottes; houtsoort; afwerking; greep type; etc. 
keukenbladen van hout of steen zijn eveneens mogelijk. 
en plaatstaal zijn we inmiddels ook erg bedreven in. voor open vakken combinaties of als corpus voor uw keukenkast met houten of fenix deurtjes.
.
goed. dat. en nog enorm veel ander maatwerk en #design voor uw interieur natuurlijk. schitterende meubels; verlichting en woonaccessoires. 😌
.
fijne avond. 😘
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

taidenäyttely seksuaalista hyväksikäyttöä kokeneiden kuvista. olemme käynnistäneet projektin, jonka pyrkimyksenä on kartoittaa seksuaalista hyväkaikäyttöä kokeneiden taidetyöskentelyä ja tuoda sitä näkyväksi yleisölle taidenäyttelyn muodossa. teoksia kerätään suomessa asuvilta aikuisilta, jotka ovat käsitelleet omia henkilökohtaisia kokemuksiaan aiheesta taidetoiminnan kautta. kerätystä teoskokonaisuudesta kuratoidaan näyttely, jonka on suunniteltu toteutuvan viimeistään keväällä 2019. projekti on jo käynnissä, sille on varmistunut useita yhteistyötahoja ja teoksia kerätään parasta aikaa. etsimme kuitenkin projektille lisää tukea, eli

text:
przeglądając ostatnie oferty wydawnicze można zauważyć wysyp książek reklamowanych jako „damskie odpowiedzi na…” lub feministyczne. sama nie wiem, czy to nowy trend, który wypłynął po fali #metoo, czy wcześniej po prostu nie zwracałam na to uwagi. problem polega na tym, żeby odróżnić pozycje, które podawane są za feministyczne, od tych naprawdę poruszających daną tematykę. "byłyśmy dziewczynami, które nie lubią się wyróżniać. które kochają się potajemnie w kolegach, ale nie mają odwagi, żeby zrobić pierwszy krok. które siedzą spokojnie na lekcjach i zbierają przyzwoite oceny, modląc się w duchu, żeby nikt nie kazał im tłumaczyć symboliki w dwunastym wersie poematu. krótko mówiąc, byłyśmy grzecznymi dziewczynkami." „moxie” to książka pozbawiona dodatkowej ilości cukru i słodyczy, które można zaobserwować w innych powieściach młodzieżowych. to odważny apel do młodych kobiet, że jesteśmy czymś więcej niż „zrób kanapkę”, czy ładną otoczką. to wezwanie do wspierania siebie nawzajem pomimo krążących stereotypów. to jedna z tych książek, które chciałabym przeczytać jako nastolatka i z pewnością przekaże ją młodszej siostrze. bo wszystkim nam nie zamkną ust. nie stłamszą wszystkich. dopóki pozostanie choć jedna z panien moxie, to kobiety będą walczyć o swoje prawa!

text: donald palmerine witnessed a sexual assault in 1969 and decided earlier this month to tell his story publicly in an essay published by the @washingtonpost earlier this month. palmerine details how he attended a party when he was 17 and witnessed the rape of an unconscious woman. for the next 50 years, he was silent though the guilt stayed with him. when dr. christine blasey-ford testified before the senate judiciary committee, he was compelled to tell this story and encourage men to speak up in the era of the #metoo movement: "i wanted to tell this story because i believe it's time for men to tell the truth about the ways they've abused women and what our role has been in creating a culture that tolerates this"

text:
my fellow female farmer @tara.b.coronado inspired me to share a bit about my mental health journey today in honor of #mentalhealthmonday. 💕
i constantly struggle with anxiety. it used to be much much worse. i haven’t suffered a panic attack since 2015. 💕
much of my anxiety stems from being assaulted four times during my early 20s and witnessing the death of a child in a horrible accident. because of these experiences, i struggled with intimacy and suffered from what i think was ptsd. i took those experiences and wrote about them in the television show i produced. it was cathartic and helped me heal. 💕
i knew that if i hid from these parts of my story, they would find me and eat me alive. i had to face them head on and share them with others in order to accept them as a part of who i am. 💕
i’ve chosen to see my time in chicago as a huge push from the universe to leave and get to this rural life i feel so blessed to live now. the farm and the animals ground me, quite literally. i feel that my journey has lead me right where i need to be.💕
when anxiety does show up, i breathe through it and focus on the present moment. i remind myself i’m worthy of love. i say to myself i am safe. then i go get a hug from paul. 💕
it’s so important to share this type of stuff. i hope in sharing today, you feel less alone in your struggle with anxiety. #wearebettertogether 💕
#mentalhealthawareness #mentalhealth #anxiety #anxietyhelp #farmlifebestlife #iamcountryside #metoo #survivor #abundancemindset #naturetherapy #farmingtherapy #gardentherapy #farmher #thisiswomenswork
name: Kelsey Jorissen
tweet_full:
my fellow female farmer @tara.b.coronado inspired me to share a bit about my mental health journey today in honor of #mentalhealthmonday. 💕
i constantly struggle with anxiety. it used to be much much worse. i haven’t suffered a panic attack since 2015. 💕
much of my anxiety stems from being assaulted four times during my early 20s and witnessing the death of a child in a horrible accident. because of these experiences, i struggled with intimacy and suffered from what i think was ptsd. i took those experiences and wrote about them in the television show i produced. it was cathartic and helped me heal. 💕
i knew that if i hid from these parts of my story, they would find me and eat me alive. i had to face them head on and share them with others in order to accept them as a part of who i am. 💕
i’ve chosen to see my time in chicago as a huge push from the universe to leave and get to this rural life i feel so blessed to live now. the farm and the animals ground me, quite literally. i feel that my journey has lead me right where i need to be.💕

text:
#metoo: 26 साल पहले महिलाओं की ख़ामोशी को आवाज़ देनेवाली योद्धा|
उम्र के तकाजे से ज़्यादा यह उसके हालात और आपबीती को बयां करता है. भंवरी देवी के चेहरे पर उभरी झुर्रियो में उस दौर के '#metoo आंदोलन' के अल्फ़ाज़ दर्ज हैं.
राजस्थान में जयपुर के निकट भटेरी गांव की भवंरी कथित रूप से उस वक्त सामूहिक बलात्कार का शिकार हुईं जब उन्होंने बाल विवाह की बुराई के विरुद्ध आवाज़ उठाई थी.
सामाजिक कार्यकर्त्ता कविता श्रीवास्तव कहती हैं, "यह महिलाओं की ओर से सितम के ख़िलाफ़ चुप्पी तोड़ने का आगाज़ था."
भंवरी देवी मामले में बेशक आरोपी बरी हो गए, लेकिन वो इंसाफ़ के लिए अपनी लड़ाई जारी रखे हुए हैं. भंवरी देवी खुद कहती हैं, "चटनी रोटी खा कर भी मैं अन्याय के विरुद्ध लड़ती रहूंगी."
name: Women Empowerment

text: bygger mitt inlägg på en bild som @mittlivsomtrasdocka la upp. ”får jag knulla din mun för rätt pris”, var mannens fråga. jag är emot mycket, men när patriarkatet och kapitalismen fattar varandras händer på ett övertydligt sätt blir jag mordisk. kvinnor säger nej. kvinnor tar plats. kvinnor är människor. men allt har ett pris! det går att kuva en kvinna med cash. om priset är rätt! om behovet av cash är såpass stort. då får man knulla en hungrig mun - om man hittar någon som inte har råd att säga nej finns oändliga möjligheter att exploatera mera. sverige är inte ett av världens mest jämställda länder. antingen är vi ett jämställt land eller så är vi inte det. världen är inte jämställd, så att prata om ”mer eller mindre jämställt” är vilseledande. världen är antingen eller. jämställd eller inte. när en man frågar en kvinna vad som är ”rätt pris” för att få utsätta henne för sexuella övergrepp, så ser vi patriarkal maktutövning at its finest. maktkapital och ekonomiska resurser att tvinga någon till underkastelse. feminismen är så jävla jobbig, man får inte längre ha sex utan samtycke eller våldta sin fru. men med lite pengar kan man köpa en minderårig t.ex och utöva makt över någon som inte har möjligheten att säga nej. jag tänker världen, jag tänker sexturism till thailand, jag tänker på männen som betalat mig och mina systrar/syskon för underkastelse. allt kan köpas för pengar, men allt kan också erbjudas för pengar.. den som är i behov har inget val. #metoo #prostitution #utanskyddsnät #intedinhora

text:
a wounded warrior-
she stumbled on her way,
tripping on her own feet,
her hands bleeding,
her soul still healing,
but all she could see was a battlefield ahead.

fighting her urge to cry,
and leading her steps to the warzone.
she moved ahead,
because she knew only she can win her fights for herself.

her legs were aching,
because she was a victim of his cruelty.
her body was shaking,
because the trauma was too much to realise.

she was still walking towards the war,
she knew she's gonna lose if she isn't strong.
the other warriors looked at her with strange eyes,
they knew something was wrong but what, they couldn't determine.

she walked to a sword,
and picked it with grace,
the pain in her parts,
was making her go insane.

she remembers how he crawled
on her skin.
looking at her like a prey in his den,
he moved forward to hunt for his little game.

with every scream,
she lost her dignity,
tear by tear,
blood by blood.

all he could see
was her innocence,
which he ripped apart from her,
because he was feeling a bit of lust.

she snapped out of her flashbacks,
and picked the sword.
with a scream in her throat,
and rage in her eyes,
she moved ahead killing all those who killed her pride.

for strangers maybe she was a lunatic,
but for those who could see the blood between her legs,
she was a wounded warrior.

#scream #english #reality #truth #bitter #wordporn #poetry #rapevictim #metoo #sad #harsh

text:
meet the arise staff! 👋

alexa perez is our outreach specialist and she has been with us for 1 1/2 years. her favorite part about arise is that they will go to the ends of the earth to help a survivor, they do not give up easily.

when asked what she thought others should know about sexual violence she said: "sexual violence isn’t just some trend on social media, it is so much more than that. sexual violence has been and will be around for a long time. but, we can cut that time short if we stop being fearful of talking about it. we must become more educated on how to not only support survivors but, how to create a world where sexual violence is basically non-existent. in the words of malala yousafzai “when the whole world is silent, even one voice becomes powerful.” #endsexualviolence #metoo #metoomovement #timesup #arisenm
name: Arise Sexual Assault Services

text:
#notallmen , but it's definitely all women. 
have you ever, for no explicable reason, been extra aware about the men around you?

i got a guide on a solo trip and he was truly helpful. he went a little out of his way, translating for me some of the things the locals said, ensuring that i got to my next destination, and such. 
little things. thoughtful things. and then he left. 
it was then that i felt foolish, because in my life when strange men help, there is (usually)  something fishy going on. not always. but self-preservation has evolved with the idea of never taking a chance. 
#womensrights #equalrights

text:
jyot se jyot jagate chalo!
.
.
i have been contemplating writing about this for a long time. is the #metoo movement only about telling our stories? sharing the details of our traumas. i agree that staying silent doesn’t help. but who do you open up to?
.
.
i love #storytelling and to a large extent understand that opening up about a trauma is one of the first steps towards our healing journey. however, to all the survivors who have shared their stories, who are contemplating and who are still not sure about it... i want to say, it doesn’t have to be social media post with a me too hashtag, it doesn’t have to be a open mic performance, you don’t need to open up to strangers if you don’t want to... you can choose to open up to a close friend or family, you can even pen it down in your diary or share it with your pet. to dispel the dark fear from within, you can take smaller steps, light just a small lamp within.
.
.
open up you must. but, you decide which way you feel comfortable and once the pain has been shared, the journey towards healing must begin. connect with communities, therapy and fellow survivors to help you on your resolve to heal yourself.
.
.
having said that, i have great respect for women who come forward to share their stories on public platforms. i acknowledge their hurt! it’s mind-numbing... my blood boils... i relive their horrors and it brings back memories of incidents i faced as a woman. it also gives strength to many who have bottled-up, repressed and silenced their pain. i read these stories not only to know what happened but also to know how they overcame the hurt, how they are healing.
.
.
this movement is larger than sharing stories. we must help ourselves and survivors to get connected to the necessary healing and advocacy resources, along the road shattering our old patriarchal culture. striving to achieve a balanced world!
.
.
#timesupnow #ibelieveher #ibelievesurvivors #metooindia #metoomovement #womenforwomen #notashamed @metoo_in #advocacy #healing #sexualassaultawareness #stopvictimblaming

text:
नवजात शिशु/the newborn
.
.
-dr.sahil .
.
dated:20/10/18
meme:@beingpoet 
tags:@capt_amarindersingh @myogi_adityanath @piyushgoyalofficial 
@manojsinhabjp
@zeenews @india.today @abpnewstv @ndtv @cnnnews18 @cnn @indiaaheadnews_in @timesnow @aajtak @officialrepublictv
@incindia @bjp4india
.
.
the issue:
while celebrating the dusshera yesterday,
a tragedy took place and still there is no one to blame.
.
.
1)the organisers knew about the lapse.
but still organised the event just to impress their leader.
.
.
2)mrs.navjot sidhu,who was the chief guest,also knew that it will happen.
but did nothing to avoid the tragedy.
she should have opted out of the event.
but she went and sealed with her visit,
the death of tons of people.
.
.
3)the police gave the clearance to organise.
.
.
4)the railway said the people trespassed their territory.
.
.
5)more than 100 died and more than 300 injured.
but the statistics are hidden due to political pressure.
.
.
6)politics is going on upon the issue.
.
.
7)the people who lost their loved ones still seek answers.
.
.
they say it's people's fault for standing upon the tracks.
but they won't admit that they organised the event at a wrong place which was vulnerable to get congested for their favourite leader was coming herself.
but the leader said that the place had been used for many years and nothing happened back then.
.
.
she meant that she was just unlucky for the incident took place in her presence and not anyone else.
.
.
and navjaat shishu says it's a big tragedy but occurred due to god's will.
he asked not to politicise the issue.
but is he willing to take the responsibility for the sins 
he and his family have committed...???
.
.
well,clap clap clap👏👏👏
.
.
p.s.a man named dalbir singh,
who played ravana that day,
also died in the tragedy.
and mrs.sidhu has nothing to say.
just one thing,
we burn the effigy of the demons every year.
but when do we burn the demons that lurk inside all of us.
.
.
.

6)politics is going on upon the issue.
.
.
7)the people who lost their loved ones still seek answers.
.
.
they say it is people's fault for standing upon the tracks.
but they will not admit that they organised the event at a wrong place which was vulnerable to get congested for their favourite leader was coming herself.
but the leader said that the place had been used for many years and nothing happened back then.
.
.
she meant that she was just unlucky for the incident took place in her presence and not anyone else.
.
.
and navjaat shishu says it is a big tragedy but occurred due to god's will.
he asked not to politicise the issue.
but is he willing to take the responsibility for the sins 
he and his family have committed...???
.
.
well,clap clap clap👏👏👏
.
.
p.s.a man named dalbir singh,
who played ravana that day,
also died in the tragedy.
and mrs.sidhu has nothing to say.
just one thing,
we burn the effigy of the demons every year.
but when do we burn the demons that lurk inside all of us.
.
.
.
  
  
     
  rain
    eaths

text:
jupiter in sagittarius// november 9
jupiter, great expander and opportunist moves signs after a heavy and deep year spent in scorpio. in scorpio jupiter gave us opportunities to speak on and begin to heal our trauma- hence the #metoo movement reaching its height during this past year (scorpio is inherently feminine and transformative).
whatever jupiter touches, expansion follows. what can we expect from its time in sagittarius? these two are naturally at home together, so it’s looking like adventure, higher learning, religious dogma, and travel are key themes. 
how is it impacting your personal chart? i’m offering an audio version of my transit reading for a special price through 11/15. you can ask me a specific question you have in mind (anything you’d like to know re: the next two months) and i will be doing a small tarot pull for you and talking about all the astro (including jupiter!) info in highlights to book. limited avail. 💥♐️
this is jupiter from a nasa telescope. irl.

#repost @justseeds

today on behalf of @survivor.love.letter we are flooding the internet with love letters to survivors of sexual assault and using the hashtag #survivorloveletter. whether you’re an ally or a survivor, we encourage you to join us in this love letter ritual and let all survivors know: not only are you believed, not only are you supported, you are loved. ✨ founded by @taniikeda 
art above and words below by justseeds artist @jessxsnow 🌸 download posters on our website ❤️
“dear survivor, you are not defined by the violence that happened to you. the earth was not defined by the asteroid that struck it but rather by the 65 million years of life that came after. you’re a brave molecule in that cosmos. our healing is slow but revolutionary. you will rise from your own ashes. your tears will flood the patriarchy and channel new rivers. you will open your new eyes for the first time and witness the stars, and their light will discover home upon your skin.

dear survivor, we are all around you. the galaxy is yours. — sibling survivor galaxy #survivorloveletter #ibelieveher #believesurvivors
.
.
.
.
.
.

#smashthepatriarchy #metoo #endtoxicmasculinity
